race.comment: CHATEAU VEGA (11) made an encouraging debut when runner-up over this trip at Mornington. Draws ideally on the fence and with natural improvement looks the leading player. WINGSANDPROPELLERS (7) debuts for the Gleeson yard and has shown good ability in his jump-outs. Expecting a forward showing. SINCERE SMILE (9) was solid first-up at Avoca when third and will strip fitter. From a strong stable and should take another step forward second-up. Stablemate TWO TO TANGO (14) is another debutant and has looked sharp in her jump-outs, winning both. Well drawn and can make an immediate impact. JELLY BEAR (12) filly by Doubtland out of Shy Talk having first start for a sharp stable. Watch the market.
